1
00:00:34,750 --> 00:00:37,208
'Cept the hot ones
never go for nice.

2
00:00:43,583 --> 00:00:46,291
[WOMAN]
Kagura! Over here!

3
00:00:46,375 --> 00:00:47,458
Huh?

4
00:00:47,541 --> 00:00:50,708
[panting]

5
00:00:50,791 --> 00:00:53,541
Ugh... Way to
show up on time, Yomi.

6
00:00:53,625 --> 00:00:55,791
Sorry. I got here
as soon as I could.

7
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:57,750
A call came through
that just couldn't wait.

8
00:00:57,833 --> 00:01:00,541
And I guess it's too much
to ask that you text me?

9
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:04,583
[YOMI]
Hey, don't be like that.

10
00:01:04,666 --> 00:01:06,333
I come bearing gifts.

11
00:01:08,250 --> 00:01:10,083
Huh?

12
00:01:10,166 --> 00:01:11,833
Fine.

13
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:17,875
[BOTH chuckle softly]

14
00:01:17,958 --> 00:01:19,500
So, uh, we okay?

15
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:21,375
[KAGURA]
Yeah, yeah, let's go.

16
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,833
[KYOTARO]
There's an old saying...

17
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:36,541
S'posed to be pretty cool.

18
00:01:36,625 --> 00:01:37,708
That's what I hear.

19
00:01:37,791 --> 00:01:39,166
[KAGURA laughs]

20
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:44,000
[KYOTARO] "You can live
your life one of two ways."

21
00:01:57,583 --> 00:01:58,916
[KYOTARO]
You can slog through

22
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,208
believing that
miracles don't exist.

23
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:20,125
[KYOTARO] Or you can
take it as a fact

24
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:22,750
that everything's a miracle.

25
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:25,833
[rumbling]

26
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:29,333
[MALE CAPTAIN 1A]
Give me a status report!

27
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:31,625
Yes, sir!

28
00:02:31,708 --> 00:02:33,375
Captain, look!

29
00:02:34,583 --> 00:02:36,833
[MALE CAPTAIN 1A]
What the hell?

30
00:02:36,916 --> 00:02:39,791
[MALE SOLDIER 1B] Sir.
It's the parliament building!

31
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:50,833
For those of you out there
just tuning in,

32
00:02:50,916 --> 00:02:53,208
we've received confirmation
that the Parliament Building

33
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:55,708
has been hijacked
by a group of espers.

34
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:57,250
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER 1A]
The building itself is currently

35
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:59,708
suspended above
the downtown skyline.

36
00:02:59,791 --> 00:03:01,833
Area traffic will be redir--

37
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:05,083
[PROFESSOR] Season's Greetings
denizens of Tokyo.

38
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,166
[PROFESSOR] As of this
fine winter's evening,

39
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:14,583
your illustrious metropolis
will be under new management.

40
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:16,041
[CROWD gasping]

41
00:03:16,125 --> 00:03:18,458
[PROFESSOR] I'm afraid the
issue is not up for debate.

42
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,875
Anyone who wishes to survive...

43
00:03:20,958 --> 00:03:23,625
is advised to
get on their knees.

44
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:44,583
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE 1A]
Don't move! You will be shot!

45
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:51,250
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE
1A, 1B gasp]

46
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:55,000
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE
1A, 1B scream]

47
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:56,666
The plight of the complacent.

48
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,416
Peace makes knaves
and dullards of us all.

49
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:05,125
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE 1C grunts]

50
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:09,208
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE 1D groans]

51
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:12,916
Our eyes are only ever fully
open when faced with terror.

52
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,500
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE
1C, 1D gasp]

53
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:18,083
And they who rule
in ignorance court oblivion.

54
00:04:21,375 --> 00:04:22,958
[MALE PROFESSOR GUARD 1A grunts]

55
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:32,541
[chimes, door lock clicks]

56
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,666
What the hell?

57
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:48,416
Try aiming
a bit to the left.

58
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,916
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE 1F grunts]
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE 1G groans]

59
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,583
[PROFESSOR]
Well, that didn't work.

60
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:54,166
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE 1H groans]
[CROWD gasps]

61
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:56,083
Dear oh dear.

62
00:04:57,375 --> 00:05:00,041
I do seem to get around.

63
00:05:00,125 --> 00:05:01,750
[MALE SPECIAL SERVICE
1E, 1I groan]

64
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:08,958
Everyone in this room
is a hostage.

65
00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:12,833
So you'll remain...
until your constituents

66
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:15,833
relinquish the reins
to better hands.

67
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:20,416
[MALE POLICE 1A]
Ladies and gentlemen, please!

68
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:23,625
Evacuate in a calm
and orderly fashion!

69
00:05:23,708 --> 00:05:27,166
Fantastic. Move it, assholes,
I got places to be.

70
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:29,250
[MALE ESPER 1A]
You're not the only one.

71
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:30,791
[gasps]

72
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,750
[MALE TAXI DRIVER 1A]
Oh, uh. Thanks.

73
00:05:41,458 --> 00:05:43,208
[CROWD gasps]

74
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:45,750
There's been an explosion
in front of Yotsuya.

75
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:48,250
I need a fire brigade, stat.

76
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:51,500
[MALE ESPER 1A laughs intensely]

77
00:05:51,583 --> 00:05:53,500
[CROWD screams]

78
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,750
[CROWD screams]

79
00:05:58,666 --> 00:06:00,208
[MALE TV STAFF 1A]
Where's our goddamn chopper?

80
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:02,291
She's fueling up, chief!
Gimme half an hour!

81
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,125
[FEMALE TV STAFF 1A]
Uh, guys?

82
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:06,333
Apparently there's
bombs going off now?

83
00:06:06,416 --> 00:06:07,583
[MALE TV STAFF 1A]
Are you kidding me?

84
00:06:07,666 --> 00:06:09,583
What? They hit
Roppongi Hills?

85
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:11,291
Holy shit!

86
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:13,291
[MALE OFFICIAL 1A]
So what do we do?

87
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:16,041
The hostages factor out walking
in through the front door.

88
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:17,416
[MALE OFFICIAL 1B]
We can't launch an offensive

89
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,833
until they're
out of harm's way.

90
00:06:18,916 --> 00:06:20,208
[MALE OFFICIAL 1C] And I can't
assemble a rescue team

91
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:22,291
with all my men
out there chasing fires!

92
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,125
[MALE OFFICIAL 1D] What are
we paying the police for?

93
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:26,416
[MALE OFFICIAL 1E] Do we have
any intel on these people?

94
00:06:27,041 --> 00:06:29,875
Right. I want the PDC
put on this immediately.

95
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:32,875
Division One is en route with
countermeasure artillery, sir.

96
00:06:32,958 --> 00:06:35,083
Send in Division Four!

97
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:37,875
[alarm blares]

98
00:06:37,958 --> 00:06:39,291
[MALE ANNOUNCER 1A]
Breaking news this hour.

99
00:06:39,375 --> 00:06:41,833
Several explosions have
rippled throughout Tokyo,

100
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:43,708
believed to be the work
of the same terrorists

101
00:06:43,791 --> 00:06:45,500
holding the Parliament
Building hostage.

102
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:47,333
Police give no
comments as to motive,

103
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:49,416
but are cautioning
residents to stay alert.

104
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,333
As the explosions
appear to be cropping up

105
00:06:51,416 --> 00:06:53,000
more or less at random.

106
00:06:53,083 --> 00:06:55,458
It's hard to substantiate
this right now, of course.

107
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,000
But the alleged
ringleader behind

108
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:59,708
these acts of terrorism
is believed to be the same man

109
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:03,416
responsible for last June's
tanker incident in Tokyo.

110
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:05,708
Citizens in districts
under evacuation

111
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:08,250
are urged to cooperate
with emergency personnel

112
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:11,916
and move in an orderly fashion
toward designated shelters.

113
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:14,666
Huh?

114
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:34,500
[train horn blares]

115
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:43,291
That puts espers at one.
Mankind, zero!

116
00:07:45,125 --> 00:07:46,541
Okay, well.

117
00:07:46,625 --> 00:07:48,625
Hopefully this
gives you some idea.

118
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,375
As you can see,
the scope of the damage

119
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:54,750
is just unbelievable, and
things continue to escalate--

120
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:56,916
Whoa! That was
another explosion!

121
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,875
[MALE POLICE 1C] Don't panic!
I repeat, do not panic!

122
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:01,583
I hate to say it, but...

123
00:08:01,666 --> 00:08:03,250
...this reporter sees
no alternative

124
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:05,500
to giving the terrorists
whatever they want.

125
00:08:05,583 --> 00:08:07,625
With the so-called
"White Girl" MIA,

126
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:10,375
how can normal humans
hope to stand against them?

127
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:13,625
Who can possibly
defend us in her place?

128
00:08:14,583 --> 00:08:16,375
She'll make a move soon,
I know it!

129
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:18,041
How do you know
she wasn't quarantined

130
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:20,208
by the new ESP legislation?

131
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:24,041
[helicopter blades hum]

132
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:29,583
New development, folks!

133
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:31,000
Some kind of special.

134
00:08:31,083 --> 00:08:33,000
I assume military plane
is bearing down

135
00:08:33,083 --> 00:08:34,875
on the Parliament Building.

136
00:08:34,958 --> 00:08:37,583
With any luck I ruled out
the White Girl too soon.

137
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:39,458
Perhaps she and
her remarkable associates

138
00:08:39,541 --> 00:08:41,791
are here to save the day!

139
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,125
All right, listen up!

140
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:55,791
First, our primary concern
is the hostages.

141
00:08:55,875 --> 00:08:59,166
Meaning stealth.
We rope down like ghosts.

142
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:01,291
Second, our enemy is powerful.

143
00:09:01,375 --> 00:09:03,375
We're talking espers
with an axe to grind.

144
00:09:03,458 --> 00:09:05,583
I shouldn't have to tell you--
[groans]

145
00:09:05,666 --> 00:09:07,625
[DIVISION 1 SOLDIER 1A]
Captain!

146
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:16,875
[DIVISION 1 SOLDIER 1A]
You'll pay for that!

147
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:18,791
She isn't onboard.

148
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:22,625
[FEMALE REPORTER 1A gasps]

149
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,750
[TORU] Freeze. Why's a cute
little thing like you

150
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,333
wielding a pair of katana?

151
00:09:48,541 --> 00:09:50,375
I said freeze!

152
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,541
[TORU gasps]

153
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,666
We've got a live one.

154
00:10:06,208 --> 00:10:07,708
[TORU]
If you're feeling frisky,

155
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:10,083
by all means, try your luck.

156
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:15,583
[gasps]

157
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:20,166
Huh?

158
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,791
[grunts lightly]

159
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,541
Agent Seventy-seven to HQ.

160
00:10:40,625 --> 00:10:42,625
Staring down
an esper as I speak.

161
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:45,500
[MAMI] Copy, Seventy-seven.
The orders haven't changed.

162
00:10:45,583 --> 00:10:47,083
All espers are
to be terminated

163
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:49,000
with extreme
prejudice on sight.

164
00:10:49,083 --> 00:10:51,416
The higher-ups
have declared open season.

165
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,000
Fire to your heart's content.

166
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:54,583
[radio static]

167
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:56,916
That makes things
simple, I guess.

168
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:06,666
[radio beeping]

169
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:08,291
[MASAKI] Agent Fifty-five
to Seventy-seven.

170
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:09,958
You're comin' in
loud and clear.

171
00:11:10,041 --> 00:11:11,458
What's up, Masaki?

172
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:12,625
[MASAKI]
According to my records,

173
00:11:12,708 --> 00:11:14,083
the girl you're
facing off with is one of

174
00:11:14,166 --> 00:11:15,583
the Professor's lackeys.

175
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:17,500
You might wanna
capture her alive.

176
00:11:17,583 --> 00:11:19,791
[TORU] No guarantees.
She's a Teleporter.

177
00:11:19,875 --> 00:11:22,208
I'll be lucky to
capture her at all.

178
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:23,791
--Here's the plan.
--[NATSUKI] Yeah?

179
00:11:23,875 --> 00:11:25,166
On my signal
I'm gonna need you

180
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,666
to aim your bike
at the target.

181
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:28,208
Sure thing.

182
00:11:28,291 --> 00:11:29,833
I don't know what you think
that'll accomplish, but okay.

183
00:11:29,916 --> 00:11:31,333
[TORU]
Just trust me.

184
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,500
Dismount and let 'er fly!

185
00:11:59,541 --> 00:12:01,375
Good work, Natsuki!

186
00:12:03,708 --> 00:12:06,958
What does he not understand
about "capture alive"?

187
00:12:07,041 --> 00:12:09,416
Please continue
to watch over us.

188
00:12:12,708 --> 00:12:14,500
I seriously loved that bike.

189
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:17,750
Yeah, I know.
Take an I.O.U.?

190
00:12:26,958 --> 00:12:29,250
Please return, Minami.

191
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:34,625
[PROFESSOR]
No need for haste.

192
00:12:34,708 --> 00:12:37,250
Our friend will
show herself in due time.

193
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:38,875
[MINAMI]
Right.

194
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,583
Uh... The hell
are we starin' at?

195
00:12:45,458 --> 00:12:47,250
[PROFESSOR chuckles]

196
00:12:50,083 --> 00:12:52,083
[NATSUKI gasps]

197
00:12:52,166 --> 00:12:54,166
Okay, sure.

198
00:12:56,416 --> 00:12:58,833
[TORU] These guys are
starting to piss me off.

199
00:12:59,375 --> 00:13:02,791
[helicopter blades hums]

200
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:04,666
[MALE CAPTAIN 1B] Attention
all radicals occupying

201
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:06,083
the parliament building.

202
00:13:06,166 --> 00:13:08,958
This government does not
negotiate with terrorists.

203
00:13:09,041 --> 00:13:12,291
There will be no deals.
I repeat: no negotiations.

204
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:15,416
No deals. If you do not release
the hostages immediately

205
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,500
we will open fire.

206
00:13:23,916 --> 00:13:25,833
[MALE CAPTAIN 1B]
This is your final warning.

207
00:13:25,916 --> 00:13:27,208
You have to the count of five

208
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:29,666
to lay down your
weapons and surrender.

209
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:32,583
One. Two. Three.

210
00:13:39,208 --> 00:13:41,708
[PROFESSOR] I was beginning
to wonder whether mankind

211
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:44,958
would bare its fangs. Heh.

212
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,208
[MALE SOLDIER 1C]
Huh?

213
00:13:50,166 --> 00:13:52,375
[MALE SOLDIER 1C, 1E, 1D gasp]

214
00:14:08,958 --> 00:14:10,250
[SALARY MAN 1A]
Damn espers!

215
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:13,625
We should've wiped them out
when we had the chance!

216
00:14:13,708 --> 00:14:16,416
[GIRL 1A] Don't worry, Mom.
Big Sis will come, just wait.

217
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,208
[MOTHER 1A]
"Big Sis"?

218
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:20,083
Mm-hm.

219
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:24,916
--[GIRL 1A] Her.
--[MOTHER 1A] Oh.

220
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,250
She always shows up.

221
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,958
Whenever people
are hurt and need help,

222
00:14:28,041 --> 00:14:30,083
the White Girl comes in
and saves the day!

223
00:14:30,166 --> 00:14:32,375
Should I know
who she's talking about?

224
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:35,125
Some kind of hero, I think,
not sure if she's real.

225
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:37,250
The White Girl is very real.

226
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:39,166
She saved my best friend's life.

227
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:41,625
I saw it happen
with my own two eyes.

228
00:14:41,708 --> 00:14:43,000
[GIRL 1A]
Really?

229
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:45,291
[SALARY MAN 1A] You think
she's comin' to save us?

230
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:48,458
Hell, far as I'm concerned
she's what we need savin' from!

231
00:14:48,541 --> 00:14:51,125
Her kind are
a damned aberration!

232
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:57,625
Walk a mile in their shoes
and then see how you feel.

233
00:14:57,708 --> 00:15:00,291
It's not fair to
write 'em all off.

234
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:04,750
Don't you worry,
she'll be here.

235
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,541
I know for a fact
she's not the type

236
00:15:06,625 --> 00:15:09,125
to excuse herself from a fight.

237
00:15:12,125 --> 00:15:13,458
You mean that?

238
00:15:13,541 --> 00:15:16,250
Are you friends with her,
do you actually know her?

239
00:15:17,916 --> 00:15:20,208
Hm.

240
00:15:20,291 --> 00:15:21,583
He's full of shit.

241
00:15:21,666 --> 00:15:24,958
Tell us another one, smartass.
She your girlfriend?

242
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:27,833
Even if she does
give a damn about us,

243
00:15:27,916 --> 00:15:31,166
what the hell
is one girl gonna do?

244
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:34,833
She's not in this
by herself. Uh!

245
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:38,958
[AYUMU]
Murasaki!

246
00:15:39,041 --> 00:15:41,125
[MURASAKI]
Ayumu!

247
00:15:41,208 --> 00:15:42,458
What're you doing?

248
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:44,500
You actually came out
all this way on your own?

249
00:15:44,583 --> 00:15:45,958
[MURASAKI]
Yeah.

250
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:48,333
[MURASAKI]
I couldn't just sit there

251
00:15:48,416 --> 00:15:50,833
and watch all this happen.

252
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,500
I don't suppose you know...

253
00:15:54,583 --> 00:15:56,291
what they might've
done with Rinka?

254
00:15:56,375 --> 00:15:58,583
Mm-mm.

255
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,875
Don't worry! C'mon,
you know how she is.

256
00:16:00,958 --> 00:16:02,458
Nobody could ever
keep her down!

257
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:05,083
She's not gonna
just sit there either.

258
00:16:06,125 --> 00:16:07,833
Yeah, you're right.

259
00:16:07,916 --> 00:16:09,541
[MURASAKI]
Hey!

260
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:14,958
There's some good luck for us!

261
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:16,208
As long as I have one of these,

262
00:16:16,291 --> 00:16:18,833
I can monitor
what they're planning!

263
00:16:18,916 --> 00:16:21,958
Your psychometry trick
does come in handy.

264
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:24,083
Hold up, I'll go you
one better.

265
00:16:24,166 --> 00:16:26,458
I know Peggy's still alive.

266
00:16:28,541 --> 00:16:30,041
Where have you been tonight?

267
00:16:30,125 --> 00:16:32,416
The city's a warzone and you're
taking in the freakin' sights?

268
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,750
[MURASAKI]
Sort of.

269
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:35,666
Don't "sort of" me!
What were we supposed to do

270
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:37,333
if something
happened to you?

271
00:16:37,416 --> 00:16:38,916
And what if something
happened to you?

272
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,500
I told you I'm not
just gonna stay put.

273
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:46,791
It's not much,
but I'm doing what I can!

274
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:48,708
[AYUMU sighs]

275
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:05,291
[MURASAKI gasps]

276
00:17:05,375 --> 00:17:06,458
[AYUMU]
What do you see?

277
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:07,708
They're gonna let it go!

278
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:10,083
They're gonna drop
the Parliament Building!

279
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:14,875
[MURASAKI]
Where are you going?

280
00:17:14,958 --> 00:17:17,500
My mother's in there!
I've gotta get her out!

281
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:19,791
[GIRL 1A]
Are you still here?

282
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:26,500
Oh! There you are! Hey!

283
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:28,416
Is that that girl?

284
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,958
When you see Big Sis,
can you tell her something

285
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:34,083
for me? I just
want her to know...

286
00:17:34,166 --> 00:17:37,250
that we all love her
very, very much!

287
00:17:39,916 --> 00:17:43,458
Because of all of the nice
things that she does for us!

288
00:17:45,708 --> 00:17:48,708
Tell her thanks! Okay?

289
00:17:49,791 --> 00:17:51,416
[MURASAKI gasps]

290
00:17:54,041 --> 00:17:55,958
[AYUMU yells]

291
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:01,208
[SALARY MAN 1A yells]

292
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,125
[AYUMU groans]

293
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:13,458
[FEMALE ESPER 1A]
Sorry 'bout that, normal peeps.

294
00:18:13,541 --> 00:18:15,500
Are we all okay?

295
00:18:15,583 --> 00:18:17,041
[laughs]

296
00:18:17,125 --> 00:18:20,083
[FEMALE ESPER 1A] My goodness!
You're hardy as cockroaches!

297
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:22,583
Oh, well. Let's try again.

298
00:18:25,958 --> 00:18:30,166
[beeping]

299
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:32,375
[FEMALE ESPER 1A]
In just five widdle minutes

300
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:34,833
I'm blowin' this place
to kingdom come!

301
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:37,125
[PEOPLE gasp]
[FEMALE ESPER 1A laughs]

302
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:38,708
Mommy!

303
00:18:38,791 --> 00:18:40,333
Damn kid.

304
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:43,000
[FEMALE ESPER 1A gasps]

305
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:45,583
Not on my watch!

306
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:49,500
What the--?

307
00:18:49,583 --> 00:18:51,916
Nuh-uh! Gotta keep
these darlings

308
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,750
sealed in for freshness!

309
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:57,583
[yelps]

310
00:18:57,666 --> 00:19:00,291
Mommy, no! Mommy!

311
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:01,791
Get away from here, Nana!

312
00:19:01,875 --> 00:19:03,250
Run far away!

313
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:04,458
[FEMALE ESPER 1A]
Oh, stop.

314
00:19:04,541 --> 00:19:07,875
You are just breaking
my heart with this.

315
00:19:07,958 --> 00:19:10,791
There, there, doll.
Don't you fret over mummsie.

316
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:13,208
She's about to be
her own constellation.

317
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:15,916
♪ Twinkle-twinkle little star! ♪

318
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,666
Uh. What is wrong with you?
These are people!

319
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:21,750
Drop this force field
and let them go!

320
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:23,125
I'll take it down.

321
00:19:23,208 --> 00:19:25,291
About five seconds
before she goes boom.

322
00:19:25,375 --> 00:19:28,041
I mean, I'm not ready
to meet my maker yet.

323
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,666
[AYUMU gasps]

324
00:19:31,083 --> 00:19:32,916
Please, ya gotta
do something!

325
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:37,750
My mommy's in there!
Help us! Mommy!

326
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:39,083
Get her out of here!

327
00:19:39,166 --> 00:19:41,833
Take my daughter
somewhere safe!

328
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:43,458
[sobbing]

329
00:19:43,541 --> 00:19:45,916
Do this for me, please!

330
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,208
Mommy!

331
00:19:48,291 --> 00:19:50,458
No! Let go of me!

332
00:19:50,541 --> 00:19:53,000
We can't leave her in there!

333
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:57,250
[MURASAKI grunting]

334
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:59,291
[AYUMU]
Murasaki. What are you?

335
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:01,291
We gonna roll over
and take this?

336
00:20:01,375 --> 00:20:03,541
I don't think so! Not today!

337
00:20:03,625 --> 00:20:13,583
[MURASAKI grunting]

338
00:20:15,625 --> 00:20:17,000
[AYUMU grunting]

339
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:19,041
[FEMALE ESPER 1A] Now this
is just getting awkward.

340
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:20,750
Use your head, kiddies:

341
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:23,000
the operative word here
is "force-field."

342
00:20:23,083 --> 00:20:24,916
Put some "upmh" into it!

343
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,000
[laughing]

344
00:20:27,083 --> 00:20:29,041
[KUROI]
Excellent advice.

345
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:31,625
Umph happens to be
my specialty.

346
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:33,458
And since you're
so hungry for it,

347
00:20:33,541 --> 00:20:36,000
I'd be happy
to give you a taste.

348
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:42,208
[bellows]

349
00:20:42,291 --> 00:20:48,916
[FEMALE ESPER 1A yells]

350
00:20:52,583 --> 00:20:54,083
[FEMALE ESPER 1A grunts]

351
00:20:58,583 --> 00:21:01,000
Nice, Kuroi!
That gave me enough time

352
00:21:01,083 --> 00:21:02,291
to defuse the bomb.

353
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:03,833
[FEMALE ESPER 1A]
You what?!

354
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,750
[AYUMU]
Don't bother.

355
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:08,875
A gun's not gonna do
much against us.

356
00:21:08,958 --> 00:21:10,916
I mean, at least...

357
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,541
...no more than it would you.

358
00:21:12,625 --> 00:21:13,708
[FEMALE ESPER 1A]
Well son of a bitch.

359
00:21:13,791 --> 00:21:15,958
Every damn one
of you's an esper?

360
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:20,416
[CROWD murmurs]

361
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:23,916
[KUROI] Ugh. Okay, let's not
argue about this right now,

362
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,791
and just agree that
not all of us are bad.

363
00:21:27,875 --> 00:21:29,750
Sure, some espers are rotten.

364
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:31,375
But who was the
first person to step up

365
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:33,125
the last time things got ugly?

366
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:34,875
You know where
I'm goin' with this.

367
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:37,500
That idiot with the
heart of gold.

368
00:21:37,583 --> 00:21:41,083
[bellows]

369
00:21:45,416 --> 00:21:48,166
[ESPER E grunts, yells]

370
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:50,166
[MALE SOLDIER 1F, 1G yell]

371
00:21:57,875 --> 00:21:59,666
[MALE ESPER 1B yells]

372
00:22:06,166 --> 00:22:07,375
[MALE CAPTAIN 1C]
We're in over our heads!

373
00:22:07,458 --> 00:22:09,416
Full retreat! Now!

374
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,958
[ESPER E]
Huh...?

375
00:22:17,833 --> 00:22:22,916
[bellows]

376
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,666
[ESPER E grunts]

377
00:22:35,958 --> 00:22:40,875
[RINKA]
Skull-Crushing... Psy-Kick!

378
00:22:42,375 --> 00:22:45,833
[PROFESSOR] At long last.
The hero has come.

379
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:51,041
Urushiba.

380
00:24:35,375 --> 00:24:37,875
[PEGGY]
Scene Two: "Girl Meets Boy!"

